## .tactic = funcs:arrow-only

### .what
enforce arrow functions for procedures
disallow function keyword

### .where
applies to functions in modules, utilities, hooks, logic, tests
exempt class methods, dynamic this bind

### .why
ensures lexical this bound
uniform code style
better visual clarity
simplifies higher-order functions, closures, composability

### .how
#### .rules
use arrow syntax: const fn = (input) => {}
never use function keyword
use object methods for classes or api contracts
always destructure input as first arg if applicable

#### .examples
##### .positive
```ts
export const setCustomerPhone = ({ customer, phone }) => {
  return { ...customer, phone };
};

const getName = (input) => input.name;
```

##### .negative
```ts
function setCustomerPhone({ customer, phone }) {  // ðŸ‘Ž function keyword
  return { ...customer, phone };
}

export function doWork() {  // ðŸ‘Ž export with function
  ...
}
```